    "text": "&gt; what is in the physical doodads that couldn't be implemented in VR or AR\nTactile feedback? The ability to specify constraints like \"these blocks need to snap together according to a certain tiling pattern\" using _magnets_ instead of having to code up some constraints? The fact that you can make eye contact with the person across the table from you?\n\nI mean, sure, we could _eventually_ figure that stuff out with AR / VR. There's lots of cool potential there. But this DL-esq stuff feels (A) like a much nearer-term reality (ignoring market forces, granted) and (B) like it's pursuing a fundamentally different goal from just \"fill the space around you with virtual graphics\"",
